ElementDescription: Mullen Average Age Equivalent (average of visual reception age, fine motor age, receptive language age, and expressive language age (not including gross motor age))

Notes: e.g., Self-Report, Parent Form, Short Form, Revised Version

ElementDescription: The Developmental Quotient (DQ) is based on the sum of the following age equivalent transformed variables: visual reception, fine motor, receptive language, and expressive language, multiplied by 100 and divided by age at the time of the assessment. The range of possible DQ values is from 1-85.
